MonitoringLocationName: Big Sandy Creek 20m Upstream of FM 1276 Bridge
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This stream, which changes its name to Village Creek downstream of this point, is sampled at its crossing under the FM 1276 bridge, at the downstream end of the Big Sandy Creek Unit.  This site represents a headwater site within the Village Creek watershed. Two additional sites will be sampled, at approximate mid and end-points of Village Creek. Upstream of the Big Sandy Creek is the Alabama-Coushatta Indian Reservation (location of a TCEQ Clean Rivers sampling site).
